Document: OpenXRFutureResult  
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrfutureresult.rst  
Summary: Methods for managing asynchronous operations and retrieving results from OpenXR extensions.  

Method: cancel_future() → void. Cancel this future, this will interrupt and stop the asynchronous function.  

Method: get_future() → int. Return the XrFutureEXT value this result relates to.  

Method: get_result_value() → Variant. Returns the result value of our asynchronous function (if set by the extension). The type of this result value depends on the function being called. Consult the documentation of the relevant function.  

Method: get_status() → ResultStatus. Returns the status of this result.  

Method: set_result_value(result_value: Variant) → void. Stores the result value we expose to the user. Note: This method should only be called by an OpenXR extension that implements an asynchronous function.